  "text": "with p190Rho guanidine exchange factor (GEF) [CITATION_1] . Interestingly, dystrophic mice, which harbor a mutation of the ␣-2 chain of laminin [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , exhibit myelin defects resembling those in kind, but not severity, to ROCK-inhibited cultures [CITATION_4] . Similarly, cocultures from dystrophic mice exhibit short, thick, myelin segments and nuclei that are eccentrically located along the internode [CITATION_5] akin to treated cultures. These results suggest that laminin-2 may activate Rho to regulate Schwann cell myelination.",
